DXF is a 2D format so I’m assuming you want to cut the piece flat and then bend it yourself.

You will need to unfold the part in order to export it as a DXF. Onshape does have some basic sheet metal tools which should allow you to do that, but you’ll probably need to convert it to a sheet metal part first. I don’t have any experience with sheet metal in Onshape so someone else will have to help with that.

Once you have a flat part, you can right click on the face you want to export and one of the options should be “Export as DXF/DWG”.
